cs.LO, cs.FL, cs.PL, cs.DS, cs.CC

Reasoning: 
- cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) is the most likely category as the paper deals with model checking of higher-order pushdown systems against MSO and PDL logic. 
- cs.FL (Formal Languages and Automata Theory) is also a likely category as the paper deals with pushdown systems and their language recognition capabilities. 
- cs.PL (Programming Languages) is a possible category as the paper deals with propositional dynamic logic. 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is a possible category as the paper deals with nested words, which are a data structure used to capture linear time behaviours with matchings. 
- cs.CC (Computational Complexity) is a possible category as the paper discusses the complexity of the satisfiability and model checking problems for PDL.
